05/10/2006
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The ambassadors of countries on the Peace Implementation Council's steering board issued a joint statement Wednesday (October 4th), calling on BiH's politicians to focus on constitutional reforms. After the ongoing elections process is completed, parties should concentrate their efforts on reaching agreement on crucial constitutional amendments, the steering board said. (Dnevni avaz, Nezavisne novine - 05/10/06; OHR Sources - 04/10/06)
